              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Define trigonometric functions both in right-angled triangles and more generally",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Express angles in degrees",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Calculate all angles and sides of a right-angled triangle",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Definitions-of-Trig-Functions",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Definitions of Trig Functions",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Let’s take a right-angled triangle with angles ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$A$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$B$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$C$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " where ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$C$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is the right angle, and it has sides ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$AB$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$BC$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$AC$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "identifier" : "Diagram_Right Triangle",
              "type" : "image"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The trigonometric functions are defined as follows:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\sin(A) = \\frac{\\text{opposite}}{\\text{hypotenuse}} = \\frac{BC}{AC}",
            "\\cos(A) = \\frac{\\text{adjacent}}{\\text{hypotenuse}} = \\frac{AB}{AC}",
            "\\tan(A) = \\frac{\\text{opposite}}{\\text{adjacent}} = \\frac{BC}{AB}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "An easy way to remember these is the mnemonic “SOH-CAH-TOA”",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "See ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Trig-functions-identities-and-equations",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " for more details.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Inverse-Trig-Functions",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Inverse Trig Functions",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The inverse trigonometric functions are defined as follows:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\sin(\\rho) = x \\implies \\rho = \\sin^{-1}(x)",
            "\\cos(\\rho) = x \\implies \\rho = \\cos^{-1}(x)",
            "\\tan(\\rho) = x \\implies \\rho = \\tan^{-1}(x)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Note that the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\textrm{func}^{-1}$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " notation is used to denote the inverse function, NOT the reciprocal.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Sometimes these are called the arc functions, e.g. ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\arcsin(x)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\arccos(x)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\arctan(x)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Solving-Right-Angled-Triangles",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Solving Right Angled Triangles",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Just manipulate the equations above to find the unknown angles and sides.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
